descript.abstract: This is parcel data, used to represent building footprints. It is used to demonstrate extruding polygon features into 3D solids for visualization.
descript.purpose: This data was developed as part of a model created by the San Gabriel Basin Water Quality Authority to be used as a visual communication tool to support planning and decision-making by all stakeholders affected by groundwater contamination. By flying around the model in 3D, the project allows viewers to understand the concepts of groundwater contamination, giving them the knowledge to make effective decisions in planning for the cleanup of contamination as well as the prevention of future contamination problems.
descript.supplinf: The data set is provided by the San Gabriel Basin Water Quality Authority. It covers 30 cities in the eastern Los Angeles corridor and spans an area that is approximately 195 square miles with a population of about 1 million.
